ArtistDescription: Mac Demarco is a canadian singer, multi-instrumentalist, and producer. His style of music has been described as "blue wave" and "slacker rock" or by DeMarco himself "jizz jazz
The son of American Actor Will Smith, Jaden Smith broke into the music scene with a series of high profile features. His debut record SYRE was released to critical acclaim.
London House Duo Dusky rode the early 2010s house revival to success and would end up signing to Above and Beyond's Anjunadeep label. Known for their funky, tribal, deep house style.

Dennis Loyd is a producer, singer, and multi-instrumentalist from Tel Aviv. He left home for Bangkok for one year to focus on writing songs and producing music; his hit single "Nevermind" came out of these solo sessions in asia.

Combining a voice that sounds made for classic soul with cutting-edge music, Khalid is a singer/songwriter from El Paso, Texas. Since releasing his breakout single "Location", Khalid has released a string of succesful tracks.
Known for his meticulous productions and pulsating live performances, NGHTMRE has released a series of collaborations and VIP remixes that have continued to see massive play across festivals.
A rock and electro pop group from New Jersey known for their indie/dance inspired tracks, ARIZONA's latest full-length release, "Gallery" has received a strong reception from fans across the globe.

Fusing soul, funk, hip-hop, and new-wave, Grammy-nominated singer Janelle Monae has left her mark on modern R&B with an energized retro-futuristic sound wrapped in theatrical science fiction concepts.
Best known as an actor for his roles in The Wire, American Gangster, and Thor, Idris Elba has also made a name for himself in the house music scene with a series of dj sets across the globe.
A Vancouver bred electronic music duo that rose to fame in the Brooklyn Underground scene in 2012. Known for a sound that meshes guitar licks and dance floor esque electric ambiance.

The younger sister of Beyonce Knowles, Solange debuted in the early 2000s with pop-oriented contemporary R&B and grew into one of the more expectation-defying and adventurous artists of the late 2010s

Colombian reggaeton singer J-Balvin' multi-platinum selling albums have made him a top-tier latin pop crossover act whose focus has been to break the segregation of the American music industry's language barrier.

Gryffin first broke out into the scene in 2014 with a series of remixes that put him on the map for modern EDM. Upon graduating with an electrical engineering degree from USC, he moved to LA and began immersing himself in music production.
Multiple Grammy award winning singer-songwriter Kacey Musgraves combines a thoroughly country sound with infectious pop melodies and beautiful vocals.
The hip-hop alter ego of American actor and comedian Donald Glover, the projects released under the Childish Gambino moniker range from hard hitting rap tunes to R&B inspired funk pieces.
A german DJ/Songwriter, Zedd produces a blend of electro house and pop and has collaborated with a long range of high profile vocalists. Be on the lookout for his latest album dropping soon.

After being introduced by way of New York City's mid-2000s dance music scene, Sam Walker and Gavin Royce decided to team up in 2011. Six years later, having logged countless hours refining their now-signature sound and growing their impressive catalog, the duo is set to release their debut album Self Help on October 20.
Equal parts rustic folk and soulful grit, Ireland's Dermot Keneedy offers a blend of passionate, introspective songwriting remniscent of of his home town in Dublin.
An american hip-hop artist based out of Minneapolis, Minnesota, Lizzo brings together a charming blend of funk inspired soulful-R&B mixed with some clever rhymes and fresh production.
Hailing from the UK, Gorgon City's of bass-driven house music and addictive vocals has established the duo as one of the most in-demand electronic acts in the industry.
A young urban music singer, rapper, and producer hailing from Puerto Rico, Bad Bunny has been absolutely huge on the global charts and is one of the most in-demand latin singers in recent music.

Jauz is a Los Angeles-based EDM producer whose eclectic range of styles has boosted him to the trap spotlight. His music is a combination of future bass, chill trap, mixed with a contemporary club edge.
British Deep/Tech-House DJ Hot Since 82 brings tracks that have an energetic yet smooth and not-overproduced feel to them. The DJ is known for his large club presence in Ibiza.
Hailing from St. Louis, Smino produces an incredibly fresh blend of R&B and rap with a futuristic yet jazz-inspired sound. His first full-length project blkswn came out to high critical acclaim.

Creating songs with big synths and bigger hooks, Chvrches found their roots in Glasgow's indie community. They made an immediate impact on the music scene with their 2013 release The Bones of What You Believe

A French producer whos quickly risen to the forefront of the electronic music movement, Snake's tracks vary from hard hitting drops with a heavy trap influence, to more melodic tracks like his collaboration with Bipolar Sunshine
Mansionair is an indie electronic trio based out of Sydney. Their recent collaboration with Odesza on the track Line Of Sight gained them a lot of mainstream attention.

Atlanta-based rapper Gucci Mane is a trap pioneer who kicked off his storied career with a prolific run of albums and mixtapes before a prison sentence became a crucial turning point in his narrative. While incarcerated, he released more than a dozen mixtapes.
A Grammy-nominated English musician, Four Tet is known for his experimental production style combining elements of jazz, electronic, and ambient music to produce a sound thats quite unheard of.

As one of the most popular groups to emerge from the post-grunge alternative rock aftermath, Weezer received high praise for their hook-heavy guitar pop style. What truly set the the band apart was their geekiness and endearing nature which shows in their music.

A long-standing and influential figure in California's electronic music community, Bassnectar delivers a heavy, physical blend of agressive electronic, embracing styles of Bass, Dubstep, and other IDM styles.
First known for her 2016 viral-hit Alaska, Maggie Rogers combines folk, dance, and R&B into a powerfully emotional yet crowd-pleasing sound.

An American fashion designer best known as the artistic director of the Louis Vuitton Mesn collection and the CEO of Off-White, Virgil is also known for his DJ side-project and collaborations with different artists.
U.K. native Ella Mai is an R&B singer/songwriter with a casually commanding voice that gained a large following after being signed to DJ Mustard's 10 Summers label.
Formed in Houston, this trio has a sound rooted in classic soul and RnB while mixing aspects of psychedelia, dub, and music from around the world -- including thai and middle eastern influence.

In the early day's of Australia's dance music boom, Anna Lunoe's excellent track selections and charismatic stage presence behind the decks translated to her becoming known as one of the best emerging DJs in Sydney.
First having started as a theatre sound engineer, Paris based producer FKJ creates mellow-sample based electronic sounds with a variety of instrumentation.
Atlanta rapper Playboi Carti debuted with a repetitive and catchy flow like contemporaries lil uzi vert and young thug, gaining recognition in the mid-2010s as an affiliate of A$AP Mob.

SongName: things we lost in the fire
ArtistDescription: French-DJ and producer Gesaffelstein produces industrial-tinged techno and electro which has garnered him a cult following. His 2015 Coachella performance was widely regarded as one of the best electronic shows in the festival's history.
A unique blend of R&B and Electronica comes from the UK's Blood Orange, who places an emphasis on powerful underlying themes within his music.
A Norwegian Indie pop-rock band with catchy pop sensibilities.
Platinum-selling DJ and producer Dillon Francis last played Coachella in 2017. Since then he has expanded into the Moombahton genre and collaborated with quite a few Latin pop stars.
Similar in approach to the Weeknd and PartyNextDoor, Toronto-based duo dvsn specialize in narcotic slow jams featuring sexually frank lyrics, with vibey production and falsetto vocals.
An Australian psychedelic-rock band conceived by Kevin Parker, Tame Impala has received widespread critical acclaim for their latest album Currents, with another album expected in the summer of 2019.
English house producer/DJ Chris Lake has collaborated with a huge amount of high profile acts within the industry, and brings a hard hitting production style that translates to an emphatic live show.

Harlem Native Sheck Wes burst onto the scene in 2018 with his hit single Mo Bamba. Championed by Travis Scott and Kanye for his wildcard rhymes, the rapper brings a unique production/delivery to the trap landscape.
